The United Democratic Movement has sent condolences to the family of the party’s Eastern Cape provincial spokesperson Mabandla Gogo, who passed away earlier on Monday. Gogo also served as the party’s councillor at King Sabatha Dalindyebo Municipality. UDM leader Bantu Holomisa says Gogo was admitted to the hospital a few days ago. He says they are awaiting postmortem results, to confirm the cause of death. “Our condolences to his wife family, friends, and UDM members in general. Bon voyage Jola, you have served your party UDM with distinction. Had it not been the lockdown regulations we would have given you a hero’s farewell. May your soul rest in peace.” #UDM Eastern Cape spokesperson Cllr Mabandla Gogo has passed on. Mabandla is one of the founders of of the UDM. We are waiting for the postmortem results. Bon voyage Mntakwethu. You worked hard for our party . Our condolences to your wife , family relatives . RIP. — Bantu Holomisa (@BantuHolomisa) July 20, 2020  